When using the atlassian plugin sdk v4.2.18 under Windows, the provided batch files (for example atlassian-install-plugin.bat) do not pass the given password parameter correctly to maven:
if the given password contains an exclamation mark (e.g. "my!password") the exclamation mark is removed (here "mypassword" is passed to maven). This results in a failure to connect to the remote system, obviously. Changing the password helps but is not always possible.
Some digging in the batch files shows that "{{setlocal enableextensions enabledelayedexpansion}}" is used, the delayed expansion causes the stripping of the exclamation mark.

